MOHAMMED BIN RASHID

Global Prosperity Award

The Global Prosperity Award will honor global manufacturers who have advanced the maker movement by contributing in the creation of a transformational solution to any of the world’s most pressing issues, and advancing at least one of the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).
  1. Sponsors of every challenge will be shortlisted for the Global Prosperity Award
  2. All challenge solutions will be assessed independently for their socio-economic impact
  3. The award is given to the adopting GMIS Partner who sponsored the solution that has, or has the potential, of making the largest global impact

Mohammed Bin Rashid Al Maktoum

We believe in the power of innovation to transform global economies, and bring prosperity to people across the world.

Examples of Honoring Our Shared Values

r
Resilience

Fostering innovation and the ability to continuously adapt.

  • Creating manufacturing-led incubators to build community "capital" in new markets
  • Using open innovation platforms to encourage young entrepreneurs with poor access to costly IP
c
Community

Creating opportunities through collaboration and partnership.

  • Creating a broad public-private ecosystem to address high priority social needs
  • Collaborative global R&D programs that help strengthen emerging market universities
  • Opening up a closed IP system
H
Harmony

Living in harmony with our environment and with each other.

  • Making industrial green-tech affordable to emerging markets
  • Creating incentives for sustainable supply chains that build on unique local human capabilities
D
Dignity

Empowering human purpose through meaningful work.

  • Shifting production to where raw materials are sourced
  • Scaling retraining programs for factory workers displaced by technology

Award recipients receive:

Global Recognition
Featured Stroies
Gifted Global Maker Challenge
Global recognition for their achievement
  • $1,000,000 USD Cash prize will be donated to an MBR Global Maker Challenge on behalf of the Global Prosperity Award winner
  • The award ceremony will involve a trip by His Royal Highness to an event on the site of the innovation (e.g. at the winning factory)
  • Feature story in our media partner (Economist, Financial Times) with ongoing media relations campaign supported by agency program
  • Deeper content on our digital platforms (also generated with agency support)
  • The right to sponsor a challenge in the MBR Global Maker Challenge
  • Award statue for each member of team leading winning program.
